{
  "stem": "24111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I had to work, it was-- I was living in a different world.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So, coming back on Sunday, that was the-- the time I looked always forward to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, this was after, because I worked-- actually, I was not working in a work camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was sleeping at home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had to come only every morning to the work place, and every evening I had to leave.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was-- right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'Free' under quotation marks, because I had to go the next day to an German construction firm, which-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which took me as a worker, as a unpaid worker, as a laborer, for nothing.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I was under the control of the Gestapo, because I had to be every morning there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had records.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had to work six days a week.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was only allowed to go home in the evening to sleep.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And only my Sunday was free.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was actually the biggest privilege we had.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It went 'til a few days before November 21st, 1941, when I left Austria and escaped to Yugoslavia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'41.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "November the 21st, 1941.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that I would like to tell you a little bit more about.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When my cousin Ernst came to me and said, Bob, my family is leaving for Shanghai on the Trans-Siberian railway from Vienna to Harbin and from Harbin to Shanghai, you have to leave, and I have to give you some other news.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Your name came up on the next list of the transport to Poland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew quite a bit.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, we knew that the Viennese Gestapo asked the Jewish community, the [NON-ENGLISH], for lists, and particular lists in 1,000 names.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he worked in the department which had all those lists.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
